The {{nihongo|'''''an'''''|案}} is a small [[table (furniture)|table]], desk or platform used during [[Shinto]] ceremonies to bear offerings. It may have four, eight or sixteen legs; the eight-legged variety, called {{nihongo|''hassoku-an'' or ''hakkyaku-an''|八足案, 八脚案||lit. "eight-legged table"}}, is the most common.

