'''`Alí-Muhammad Varqá''' ({{lang-fa|{{big|علي محمد ورقا}}}};&lrm; 1911{{spaced ndash}}September 22, 2007) was a prominent adherent of the [[Bahá'í Faith]]. He was the longest surviving [[Hand of the Cause|Hand of the Cause of God]], an appointed position in the Bahá'í Faith whose main function is to propagate and protect the religion on the international level.
Varqá was born in 1911 in [[Tehran, Iran]] to a well-known [[Iran]]ian Bahá'í family. His grandfather [[Varqá|Mírzá `Alí-Muhammad Varqá]], from whom he received his name, was an [[Apostles of Bahá'u'lláh|Apostle of Bahá'u'lláh]], and his father, [[Valíyu'lláh Varqá]], was also a Hand of the Cause.<ref name="bwns">{{cite web | url = http://news.bahai.org/story/579 | title = Baha'i world loses most distinguished member | date = 2007-09-24 | accessdate = 2007-09-24 | publisher= Baha'i World News Service}}</ref>
Varqá moved to Paris and studied at the [[University of Paris|Sorbonne]], where he obtained a [[doctorate]] in 1950. He then returned to Iran and taught at the universities of [[University of Tehran|Tehran]] and [[University of Tabriz|Tabriz]]. During this time, he also served in various [[Bahá'í administration|administrative]] capacities in the Bahá'í community of Iran.<ref name="bwns" />
After his father's death, Varqá was appointed as a [[Hand of the Cause]] by [[Shoghi Effendi]] on November 15, 1955.<ref>{{cite book | title = Messages to the Baha'i World: 1950-1957 | first = Shoghi | last = Effendi | publisher = Bahá'í Publishing Trust | location = Wilmette | year = 1971 | isbn = 0-87743-036-5 |url=http://bahai-library.com/shoghieffendi_messages_bahai_world}}</ref> He served in that capacity for 52 years until his death in 2007, and was the last surviving Hand of the Cause. As part of his role, he travelled to many countries, and attended the first Bahá'í national conventions of many countries including [[Belgium]] and [[Central African Republic]]. He also served as the trustee of [[Huqúqu'lláh]] since 1955, a role which his father also held.<ref name="bwns" />
In 1979, he moved to [[Canada]] and later moved to [[Haifa]], [[Israel]] where the [[Bahá'í World Centre]] is located. He died on September 22, 2007 in Haifa and was buried in the Bahá'í cemetery there.<ref name="bwns" />
